            <div class="comment_body">
                                                                                                                
                I don't do competitio<wbr/>&shy;ns, but I have a trailer mounted smoker--a big mother--an<wbr/>&shy;d the most important point made in this article is that falling off the bone does NOT indicate a good rib. All that means is that it was overcooked<wbr/>&shy;, and the sinew which holds the meat to the bone was burned away.<br />
<br />
However, I never in my life heard of putting cooking oil on the ribs first. If he does that to hold the rub, I just don't think it's necessary.            </div>
            
